In .NET MAUI, those `Application`-level overrides are replaced by **`Window` lifecycle events**. The recommended approach is to create a custom `Window` subclass:

```csharp
public class MyWindow : Window
{
    public MyWindow(Page page) : base(page) { }

    protected override void OnCreated()    { /* was OnStart  */ }
    protected override void OnResumed()    { /* was OnResume */ }
    protected override void OnStopped()    { /* was OnSleep  */ }
    protected override void OnDestroying() { /* cleanup      */ }
}
```

Then in your `App` class, override `CreateWindow`:

```csharp
public partial class App : Application
{
    protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
        => new MyWindow(new MainPage());
}
```

**Alternatively**, for platform-specific hooks, use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android.OnStop(activity => { /* ... */ }));
#elif IOS
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios.OnResignActivation(app => { /* ... */ }));
#endif
});
```

**Quick mapping:**

| Xamarin.Forms | MAUI Window        |
|---------------|--------------------|
| `OnStart`     | `OnCreated`        |
| `OnSleep`     | `OnStopped`        |
| `OnResume`    | `OnResumed`        |
| *(none)*      | `OnDestroying`     |
